The evidence with the title 'Reforming the Banks For Good | Dissent Magazine ' says The persistence of too big to fail. The data are indisputable: the top six bank holding companies — JPMorgan Chase, Bank Of America, Citigroup, Wells Fargo, Goldman Sachs , and Morgan Stanley— are larger than they were before the 2008 crisis . Together they hold 37 percent more assets than they did five years ago. 
